%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22950%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EMike%20Gorius%2C%20left%2C%20and%20Kevin%20Hart%20buy%20real%20estate%20in%20Louisville.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20Mike%20Gorius%20and%20Kevin%20Hart%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EBusiness%20partners%20Kevin%20Hart%20and%20Mike%20Gorius%20have%20built%20a%20robust%20and%20diverse%20real%20estate%20portfolio.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ETheir%20strategy%20involves%20flipping%20and%20wholesaling%20for%20cash%20and%20holding%20rentals%20for%20long-term%20gains.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ETheir%20advice%20to%20new%20investors%20is%20to%20start%20with%20a%20flip%20to%20bring%20in%20cash%20and%20then%20expand%20to%20rentals.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EKevin%20Hart%20started%20thinking%20about%20real%20estate%20as%20a%20viable%20business%20in%20college%20when%20he%20was%20renting%20a%20duplex%20with%20his%20fraternity%20brothers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20had%20both%20sides%2C%20there%20were%2010%20guys%2C%20and%20we%20were%20all%20paying%20500%20bucks%20a%20month%20to%20this%20landlord%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20University%20of%20Kentucky%20grad%20told%20Business%20Insider.%20It%20seemed%20like%20a%20relatively%20simple%20way%20to%20bring%20in%20thousands%20of%20dollars%20a%20month%2C%20%26quot%3Bso%20I%20always%20had%20that%20in%20the%20back%20of%20my%20head.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20graduated%2C%20started%20a%20career%20in%20accounting%2C%20and%20found%20his%20mind%20wandering%20as%20he%20sat%20in%20his%20cubicle%20all%20day%20%26quot%3Bmindlessly%20sending%20spreadsheets%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BI%20was%20daydreaming%20about%20real%20estate%20or%20other%20businesses%2C%20thinking%2C%20'How%20do%20I%20get%20out%20of%20here%3F'%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHis%20curiosity%20led%20him%20to%20websites%20like%20BiggerPockets.%20He%20learned%20about%20various%20investing%20strategies%2C%20%26quot%3Bbut%20I%20put%20real%20estate%20on%20the%20back%20burner%20because%20I%20just%20thought%20it%20was%20too%20hard%20to%20get%20started.%20I%20didn't%20have%20any%20money%20and%20didn't%20think%20I%20could%20do%20it.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20career%20pivot%20to%20insurance%20in%202017%20ended%20up%20putting%20Hart%20in%20the%20red.%20He%20started%20working%20as%20an%20independent%20contractor%20for%20State%20Farm%20and%20took%20out%20a%20business%20loan%20to%20help%20with%20marketing%20expenses.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20one%20major%20silver%20lining%20was%20that%20it%20introduced%20him%20to%20home%20flippers%20in%20his%20area%20in%20Louisville.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThey%20were%20clients%20of%20mine%20on%20the%20insurance%20side%20and%20motivated%20me%20to%20flip%20a%20house%20and%20see%20if%20it's%20really%20for%20me%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Hart.%20%26quot%3BI%20started%20working%20with%20some%20local%20wholesalers%2C%20found%20a%20good%20deal%2C%20and%20bought%20this%20first%20house%20with%20%248%2C000%20down%20using%20a%20hard%20money%20lender.%20My%20wife%20was%20super%20freaked%20out%20about%20what%20I%20was%20doing%20because%20I'd%20never%20done%20it%20before.%20Luckily%2C%20it%20went%20really%20well.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20said%20he%20and%20his%20first%20business%20partner%20bought%20the%20property%20for%20about%20%2470%2C000%20in%20March%202019%2C%20put%20roughly%20%2440%2C000%20of%20work%20into%20it%2C%20and%20sold%20it%20for%20around%20%24160%2C000.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BTogether%20we%20split%20probably%20%2430%2C000%20of%20profit%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Hart.%20He%20was%20hooked%2C%20bought%20two%20more%20flips%20before%20the%20end%20of%20the%20summer%2C%20and%20quit%20his%20job%20later%20that%20same%20year.%20%26quot%3BI%20had%20these%20paychecks%20coming%20in%20that%20were%20triple%20what%20I%20was%20paying%20myself%20at%20State%20Farm%20as%20a%20self-employed%20insurance%20agent.%20That%20was%20super%20exciting.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222260%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22mike%20gorius%20kevin%20hart%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67afdf727bb3f854015d07e7%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221695%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EHart%20and%20Gorius%20have%20been%20working%20together%20on%20real%20estate%20deals%20since%202022.%20They%20formed%20an%20official%20partnership%20in%202024.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20Kevin%20Hart%20and%20Mike%20Gorius%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EHart's%20current%20business%20partner%2C%20Mike%20Gorius%2C%20took%20a%20different%20approach%20at%20the%20beginning%20of%20his%20real%20estate%20career%2C%20which%20began%20as%20a%20side%20project%20to%20help%20alleviate%20credit%20card%20debt%20and%20car%20loans.%20He%20started%20by%20purchasing%20a%20duplex%20in%20Louisville%2C%20despite%20living%20in%20Phoenix%20at%20the%20time%2C%20and%20turned%20it%20into%20a%20long-term%20rental.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20spent%20about%20%2435%2C000%20on%20the%20down%20payment%20of%20my%20own%20money.%20When%20I%20got%20my%20first%20rental%20check%2C%20the%20profit%20was%20like%20%24400%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Gorius%2C%20who%20worked%20in%20sales%20and%20recruiting%20throughout%20his%20corporate%20career.%20%26quot%3BI%20remember%20thinking%2C%20'Oh%20man%2C%20it's%20going%20to%20take%20a%20lot%20of%20%2435%2C000%20down%20payments%20for%20me%20to%20retire%20off%20this.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGorius%20and%20Hart%2C%20who%20initially%20connected%20when%20Gorius%20was%20looking%20to%20buy%20in%20the%20Louisville%20market%2C%20have%20been%20doing%20deals%20together%20since%202022.%20They%20formed%20an%20official%20business%20partnership%20in%202024%20under%20the%20Joe%20Homebuyer%20franchise%20and%2C%20in%20their%20first%20full%20year%20working%20together%2C%20did%2050%20transactions%20between%20wholesales%2C%20wholetails%2C%20and%20flips.%20They%20also%20own%20more%20than%2020%20rental%20properties%2C%20including%20short-%2C%20mid-%2C%20and%20long-term%2C%20in%20the%20Lousiville%20area.%20BI%20verified%20their%20property%20ownership%20and%20deal%20history%20by%20looking%20at%20settlement%20statements%20and%20closing%20documents.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThanks%20to%20real%20estate%2C%20Hart%20says%20he's%20completely%20rid%20of%20bad%20debt%2C%20and%20Gorius%2C%20who%20quit%20his%20corporate%20job%20in%202023%20to%20work%20in%20real%20estate%20full-time%2C%20expects%20to%20have%20paid%20off%20his%20in%202025.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere's%20not%20much%20else%20out%20there%20where%20you%20can%20make%20lump%20sum%20checks%20to%20help%20you%20pay%20off%20that%20debt%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Hart.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20a%20good%20business%20to%20help%20you%20build%20your%20savings%20account.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETheir%20next%20major%20milestone%20is%20financial%20freedom%20and%20the%20option%20to%20never%20have%20to%20work%20for%20income%20again%2C%20though%20they're%20not%20the%20types%20to%20be%20on%20the%20golf%20course%20five%20days%20a%20week.%20They%20said%20the%20flexibility%20is%20more%20intriguing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22ff59d02d-1782-48e0-88e0-0e3320bfcb5e%5C%22%3EA%20two-pronged%20wealth-building%20strategy%3A%20Flip%20to%20bring%20in%20cash%2C%20then%20buy%20and%20hold%20rentals%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EHart%20and%20Gorius%20have%20narrowed%20in%20on%20a%20real%20estate%20strategy%20that%20works%20for%20them%20%E2%80%94%20and%20they%20encourage%20new%20investors%20to%20use%20a%20similar%20approach%3A%20Start%20with%20a%20flip%20for%20a%20cash%20infusion%20and%20then%20use%20that%20money%20to%20buy%20and%20hold%20rentals.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20you%20have%2010%20grand%20you%20can%20typically%20go%20find%20a%20deal%2C%20put%20the%20down%20payment%20down%2C%20and%20hopefully%20you're%20making%20%2415%2C000%20to%20%2430%2C000.%20That's%20a%20quick%20capital%20boost%20to%20help%20you%20get%20going%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Hart.%20%26quot%3BIf%20you%20start%20flipping%20a%20few%20houses%20a%20year%2C%20whether%20you've%20got%20a%20W2%20or%20not%2C%20that's%20definitely%20going%20to%20put%20you%20in%20the%20right%20direction%20to%20be%20able%20to%20do%20other%20things%20like%20buying%20rentals.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20easier%20said%20than%20done.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20common%20and%20costly%20mistake%20in%20the%20flipping%20world%20is%20going%20with%20the%20first%20contractor%20you%20find%2C%20rather%20than%20interviewing%20a%20few.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BTry%20to%20get%20referrals%20from%20other%20flippers.%20That%20way%2C%20hopefully%2C%20you're%20not%20getting%20burned%20on%20a%20bad%20contractor%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Hart.%20%26quot%3BYou%20definitely%20don't%20want%20to%20hire%20the%20cheapest%20one%20you%20find.%20They're%20probably%20cheap%20and%20available%20for%20a%20reason.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnother%20rookie%20mistake%20is%20taking%20on%20too%20big%20of%20a%20project.%20You%20don't%20want%20to%20be%20gutting%20the%20house%20or%20moving%20walls%20on%20your%20first%20flip.%20Instead%2C%20start%20with%20more%20of%20a%20cosmetic%20flip%20where%20you're%20updating%20the%20flooring%2C%20paint%2C%20cabinets%2C%20and%20light%20fixtures.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIn%20reality%2C%20if%20you're%20doing%20a%20lot%20of%20flips%2C%20flipping%20is%20a%20pretty%20boring%20business.%20You're%20using%20the%20same%20paint%20colors%2C%20you're%20using%20similar%20flooring.%20Whatever's%20in%20style%20that%20year%2C%20we're%20like%2C%20'Okay%2C%20for%20the%20next%20five%20houses%2C%20this%20is%20what%20we're%20doing%2C'%26quot%3B%20said%20Hart.%20%26quot%3BWe're%20doing%20neutral%20colors%2C%20neutral%20floors%2C%20and%20just%20making%20everything%20fresh%20and%20clean%20so%20that%20it%20appeals%20to%20the%20most%20amount%20of%20people%20possible.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20money%20coming%20in%20from%20their%20flips%20and%20wholesales%20funds%20their%20lifestyle%20and%20savings.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BFlipping%20and%20the%20wholesaling%2C%20that's%20what%20I%20love%20to%20do.%20That's%20my%20day%20job%2C%20so%20I've%20turned%20that%20into%20my%20'salary%2C'%26quot%3B%20said%20Gorius%20%E2%80%94%20and%20it%20can%20be%20lucrative.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20cited%20their%20most%20recent%20deal%3A%20%26quot%3BWe%20got%20a%20property%20under%20contract%2016%20days%20ago%2C%20closed%20on%20it%20today%2C%20and%20wholesaled%20it%20for%20%2424%2C000.%20Because%20it's%20a%20wholesale%2C%20that's%20pretty%20much%20gross%20profit.%20That's%20an%20extreme%20case.%20That's%20a%20fantastic%20deal.%20I%20will%20say%20there%20are%20other%20deals%20and%20flips%20that%20have%20been%20in%20our%20pipeline%20for%20two%2C%20three%20months%20now%2C%20so%20they're%20not%20all%20like%20that.%20But%20that%20is%20the%20power%20of%20this%20business.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20successful%20flip%20or%20wholesale%20can%20help%20you%20build%20enough%20savings%20to%20start%20adding%20rental%20properties%20to%20your%20portfolio.%20The%20problem%20with%20starting%20with%20a%20long-term%20rental%20is%20that%20it%20likely%20won't%20generate%20much%20cash%20flow%2C%20if%20any.%20In%20their%20market%2C%20for%20example%2C%20they%20can%20profit%20about%20%24100%20to%20%24200%20a%20month%20per%20unit.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20you%20don't%20have%20any%20money%20in%20the%20bank%20and%20a%20tenant%20calls%20you%20because%20the%20water%20heater%20went%20out%2C%20there%20goes%20a%20whole%20year%20of%20your%20cash%20flow%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Hart.%20%26quot%3BYou%20really%20have%20to%20be%20prepared%20to%20be%20able%20to%20make%20these%20repairs.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThey%20look%20at%20their%20long-term%20rentals%20as%20their%20retirement%20funds.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThey%20probably%20won't%20make%20a%20ton%2C%20if%20any%2C%20money%20in%20the%20short%20term%2C%20but%20if%20you%20hold%20it%20for%20that%2020%2C%2030%20years%2C%20then%20that's%20your%20retirement%20plan%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Gorius.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20Hart%20put%20it%3A%20%26quot%3BBuying%20rental%20properties%20is%20like%20a%20slow%20burn%20to%