working%20reduced%20hours%20(with%20a%20pay%20cut).%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHaving%20so%20much%20flexibility%20means%20parents%20get%20to%20spend%20more%20time%20with%20their%20kids%20in%20the%20first%20few%20months%20of%20their%20lives.%20I%20wish%20I%20had%20more%20of%20that%20time%20with%20my%20kids%20when%20they%20were%20born%20in%20the%20US.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22e973d8ad-5e4b-4127-a587-fdeec911a696%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EChildcare%20is%20much%20more%20affordable%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20we%20lived%20in%20the%20US%2C%20we%20spent%20%241%2C800%20on%20daycare%20per%20month%20for%20our%20son.%20When%20we%20had%20our%20daughter%2C%20we%20added%20on%20%241%2C900%20for%20her%20spot%2C%20a%20little%20extra%20because%20she%20was%20an%20infant.%20That%20brought%20our%20monthly%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fwatch%3Fv%3DXksv2EGG9ek%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edaycare%20costs%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20%243%2C700%20%E2%80%94%20more%20than%20our%20mortgage.%20Being%20on%20a%20teacher's%20salary%20and%20not%20making%20that%20much%2C%20I%20sometimes%20wondered%20if%20I%20should%20drop%20out%20of%20the%20workforce%20and%20become%20a%20stay-at-home%20mom%20instead%20of%20spending%20the%20money%20on%20daycare.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20daycare%20isn't%20free%20in%20Spain%2C%20it's%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fi-moved-to-spain-for-more-affordable-childcare-2024-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ea%20lot%20more%20affordable%3C%2Fa%3E.%20We%20paid%20%E2%82%AC500%20for%20our%20daughter.%20For%20our%20son%2C%20who%20was%20old%20enough%20to%20start%20going%20to%20school%2C%20we%20chose%20to%20put%20him%20in%20the%20same%20private%20school%20his%20older%20brother%20attended%2C%20which%20cost%20%E2%82%AC300.%20For%20two%20young%20children%2C%20the%20total%20costs%20were%20%E2%82%AC800%2C%20or%20around%20%24830%20a%20month%2C%20which%20was%20easier%20for%20us%20to%20swing%20even%20with%20me%20taking%20a%20pay%20cut.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAdditionally%2C%20families%20with%20three%20or%20more%20children%20are%20entitled%20to%20a%20Tarjeta%20Familia%20Numerosa%2C%20or%20%26quot%3BLarge%20Family%20Card.%26quot%3B%20This%20card%20has%20given%20us%20many%20discounts%2C%20including%20on%20train%20tickets%2C%20groceries%2C%20electricity%20and%20water%20bills%2C%20and%20passport%20renewals.%20It%20helps%20us%20prevent%20small%20costs%20from%20snowballing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22a1e37150-2288-400e-ac02-5eb9b0b6e3af%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EIn%20Spain%2C%20kids%20are%20part%20of%20adult%20society%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221024%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Emily%20San%20Jos%C3%A9%20with%20her%20daughter.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67ae683beb4be2fff9a49f9e%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22768%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EEmily%20San%20Jos%C3%A9%20with%20her%20daughter.%3Cp%3EEmily%20San%20Jos%C3%A9%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ESpain%20feels%20more%20family-friendly%20than%20the%20US%20because%20children%20are%20more%20integrated%20into%20adult%20society.%20While%20there%20are%20still%20some%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchild-focused-parenting-bad-for-kids-parents-2024-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Echild-focused%20activities%3C%2Fa%3E%20like%20zoos%20and%20birthday%20parties%2C%20it's%20much%20more%20normal%20to%20see%20children%20in%20adult%20spaces%20like%20bars%20and%20restaurants.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20starts%20at%20school.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famerican-living-in-spain-shares-differences-in-school-2023-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ESpanish%20school%20lunches%3C%2Fa%3E%20include%20more%20adult%20meals%20like%20a%20vegetable%20pur%C3%A9e%20appetizer%2C%20a%20main%20like%20chicken%20or%20fish%20with%20rice%20or%20potatoes%2C%20and%20then%20fruit%20or%20yogurt%20for%20dessert.%20The%20kids%20are%20also%20taught%20table%20manners.%20Not%20only%20are%20they%20less%20picky%20%E2%80%94%20my%20three-year-old%20now%20likes%20salads!%20%E2%80%94%20but%20it's%20easier%20to%20bring%20kids%20to%20restaurants%20because%20they%20know%20how%20to%20behave%20in%20public.%20It's%20very%20common%20for%20kids%20to%20join%20their%20parents%20for%20dinner%2C%20staying%20up%20late%20with%20the%20grown-ups.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAdults%2C%20in%20turn%2C%20seem%20more%20accepting%20of%20kids%20in%20public%20spaces%20here%20than%20in%20the%20US.%20If%20a%20young%20child%20is%20experiencing%20a%20tantrum%20on%20the%20street%2C%20parents%20don't%20rush%20as%20much%20to%20quiet%20them%3B%20it's%20accepted%20that%20small%20kids%20have%20lots%20of%20emotions%20and%20need%20to%20express%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20experienced%20the%20opposite%20when%20we%20visited%20Oregon%20this%20past%20Christmas%20break.%20I%20took%20my%20daughter%20to%20see%20%26quot%3BThe%20Nutcracker%26quot%3B%20with%20my%20friend%20and%20her%20daughter%2C%20who%20is%20around%20the%20same%20age%20as%20mine.%20We%20took%20them%20to%20a%20coffee%20shop%20before%20the%20show%2C%20and%20the%20girls%20were%20excited%20and%20dancing%20around.%20A%20man%20looked%20agitated%2C%20so%20we%20told%20them%20to%20keep%20it%20down.%20When%20he%20got%20up%20to%20leave%2C%20he%20muttered%20%26quot%3Bbrats%26quot%3B%20at%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20such%20an%20eye-opening%20experience.%20While%20not%20everyone%20in%20America%20is%20like%20that%20man%2C%20adults%20in%20Europe%20seem%20more%20tolerant%20of%20kids.%20Sure%2C%20parents%20step%20in%20when%20their%20children%20are%20misbehaving.%20There's%20also%20a%20cultural%20understanding%20that%20kids%20are%20kids%20and%20that%20they%20belong%20in%20public%20spaces%2C%20too.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%224f7bfd4c-c8ff-44f5-b556-918e24b72e22%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3ESpain%20isn't%20perfect%2C%20but%20it's%20easier%20for%20families%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EOther%20than%20my